description:
Known for its impeccable waterfront position, Soko West End is the ideal building for the young professional lifestyle.


Boasting an extravagant panoramic-view rooftop and embellished by an infinity edge pool, bbq area and sauna, Soko lacks no luxuries for those who call this building home.


Apartment 108 has you located on courtyard level with direct access that leads you out onto the water; West End living at it's finest. The floor to three-meter ceiling windows decorate your unit with natural light as the courtyard's grand greenery provide privacy.


Lock-up and leave style, the apartment has an easy keep and clean floorplan, optimal for a busy lifestyle.


Two generous bedrooms with access to your oversized courtyard make up this residence, the master, adorned with a walk-in-robe and ensuite.


Make your way to the courtyard and you'll find yourself surrounded by beautiful greenery that provides a sense of serenity, a relief amongst inner-city suburbs.


The kitchen and bathrooms, practically designed with fantastic appliances whilst providing you ample space and storage so no sacrifices are made as you adapt to apartment-living.


Other Features Include:

- Ducted air-conditioning throughout
- Easy-clean floorboards
- 3 metre ceilings
- Secure Parking
- Shared BBQ area with gardens
- Rooftop pool with sun lounges and deck chairs


It goes without saying that West End is a thriving suburb abundant with trendy cafes, boutiques and an array of convenient transport options whether you're commuting to work by bus in the city, enjoying a day at Southbank via river-walk or ferrying out of the bubble.


I invite you to come experience all that West End and the waterfront have to offer here at Soko.


Please see our Open Home times or contact me for a private inspection.


Dane Koosmen.
